OS_CallEvery  (&3C)
#Parent OS_
=>	R0 =	time to call in cs - 1
	R1 =	pointer to address to call
	R2 =	value of R12 to be called with

<=	R0,R1 preserved
                 
Sets a routine to be triggered every time a specified delay has elapsed. The routine is entered in SVC mode with interrupts disabled. To remove use <OS_RemoveTickerEvent>.
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 431=>PRM-1:431>.
